newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine soybeans, maize, slip in CBOT's wake.
newsitem.headline: Argentine soybeans, maize, slip in CBOT's wake.

text.p: Argentine soybean and maize prices slipped in the slipstream of a lower Chicago in cash market trading at the Buenos Aires Cereals Exchange midsession, traders said.
"We were caught by surprise when Chicago fell. Supply's dried up," one trader said.

Prices paid to farmers for maize in Buenos Aires slipped $2 to $112. Buenos Aires soybeans lost $5 to $304. Sunflower prices firmed in tight trade, with bullish pressure from early harvest yields. Buenos Aires sunflower seed gained $4 to $212. Wheat was weaker in slow trade, losing $1 in Buenos Aires to $149.
